The Federal Government has declared Monday, June 14, as public holiday to mark this year’s Democracy Day celebration. Interior Minister Rauf Aregbesola announced the holiday on behalf of the Federal Government yesterday in Abuja. A statement by the Permanent Secretary in the ministry, Dr. Shuaib Belgore, quoted Aregbesola as saying that “any form of agitation that threatens the unity of the country should be shunned for the good of all”.